{
  "stem": "25639.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] When we arrived in Auschwitz, I-- I didn't know what that putrid smell is all about.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and while we didn't know where we were, what type of place it was, it was just nauseating.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I just dismissed it from my mind.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But once I learned that we were in a death camp, and once I was assigned to work just behind one of the gas chambers and crematorium, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I knew very well what this was all about.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and when my-- when I associated these columns of people who went in to gas chamber and crematorium number four, which is the one that was close by-- 20, 25 feet away from me-- I-- I knew what that smell was all about.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it affected me tremendously.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It-- it made me terribly nauseous, and I-- I was physically affected by it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I knew that I won't be able to keep up with-- keep up with this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I must get used to it, or I'll perish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then one day soon, I completely lost my sense of smell in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "For 47 years, I couldn't smell anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sense of taste remained quite keen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the doctor thought that it was probably psychological.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't think they really knew for sure.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I went through all sorts of tests, but they found nothing wrong.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It did not affect my cooking.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] It's amazing to me how the human body is able to adjust to-- to horror.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] If we really want to, we-- I think-- I think it's possible for us to go through just about anything.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
